how does a few bottles of g stout beers affect adiabetic there are some studies that have shown that having a beer results in a reduction in fasting blood sugar readings the next morning there is a risk of alcohol related hypoglycemia if you take tablets or insulin and the result can be masked by the effects of the alcohol example you could be in a state of severe hypoglycemia and your roommate thinks you're sleeping it off that result could be fatal generally speaking a diabetic may engage in moderate alcohol intake just as anyone else but there are some exceptions uncontrolled readings high blood pressure etc that may result in your doctor advising that you not drink at all this is one to discuss with your doctor just to be safe Vodka Martini cocktail Alcoholic beverage Cocktail Tequila Gin Chocolate Drinking culture Soft drink Cuisine of Denmark Distilled beverage Long Island Iced Tea Rum James Bond Gatorade Bloody Mary (cocktail) Public house Drink Blues Social rule Hangover Russian cuisine Oreo Theory of conduct Coffee Cider Breakfast Pimm's Shasta (soft drink) Moe Szyslak Coca-Cola Fanta Red Bull Absolut Vodka New York Giants RuneScape quests Fecal incontinence Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Beer Saturday Night Live Ice cream Korean cuisine Moonshine Mothers Against Drunk Driving About a Boy Humphrey Bogart Insomnia Teen Girl Squad AFI 100 Years series Drunkenness The Smoking Room Yoghurt Energy drink Anthony Burgess Punch (drink) Ty Cobb Utility Shochu Time Out of Mind The Catcher in the Rye Brian Griffin Breastfeeding Sake Dr Pepper/Seven Up, Inc. Apple Cacha__a Salmiakki Koskenkorva Grey goo Bong Hot chocolate Water Prohibition Bartender Cold Stone Creamery Customs and etiquette of Japan Cornell Hangovers House music Irn-Bru Absinthe Koskenkorva Ctrl Alt Del (webcomic) Bar (establishment) Conker's Bad Fur Day In-N-Out Burger Knots Landing Birthday Sherbet Ethylene glycol Double Nickels on the Dime Trailer Park Boys One Tree Hill (TV series) Pisco Ron